LAGOS  – A large number of elder­ly people in Ado-Odo-Ota Local Government Area of Ogun State, on Thurs­day, January 19, 2022, ben­efited from relief pack­ages donated by District 404B1 of the Lions Club International Associa­tion. The donation was made at the palaces of Oba Ab­dul-Akeem Odunaro, Olu­kotun of Otun Ota, and Oba Clement Akinyemi, Ajana of Ijana Ota, Ogun state. The donations, accord­ing to Rasheed Ologun­dudu, the club’s District Governor, was focused on relieving hunger as part of the activities lined up from December to January by the association, to give back to the society and a means of showing love to the elderlies.